==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chelone
<hw>Che*lo"ne</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chelw`nh</grk> a tortoise. So named from shape of the upper lip of
the corolla.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of hardy perennial
flowering plants, of the order <ord>Scrophulariace⟦ae⟧</ord>, natives of
North America; -- called also <altname>snakehead</altname>,
<altname>turtlehead</altname>, <altname>shellflower</altname>,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chelonethida</ent>⟦br⟧
